[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'All right, we just released a brand new animation tool in Pixelab. As you guys know, we already have tools like animation with skeleton, animation to animation, and animate with text pro. But this one is a bit different. This is animate with text V3. In the UI, you\'ll'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually see it as animate with text new. But this is basically the next generation of our text to animation system. It lets you generate animations using an image reference and a text'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt. And the best part is that it\'s actually cheaper than the pro tool. So it\'s much easier to experiment with different ideas. Let me show you a few examples. For the first example, I\'m going to use'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this cute mage character. First, we\'re going to go to the animate category and we\'re going to look for animate with text new. The animation I want is for her to take off her hat and hold it in her hands. We first have to set our reference image,'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which would be the character, and then as you can see, we can choose the amount of frames that we want for the animation. The limit changes depending on the size of your sprite. So the bigger the sprite, the less the frames, but this model gives us nice room to'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'animate even big sizes. And then we got our action description. So the prompt I\'m going to use is the cute mage takes her hat off and holds it in her hand. And there we go. You can see the'

[01:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'animation it generated. Like with a lot of generations, you might want to clean up a few frames. But once that\'s done, we can actually extend the animation. So now I\'m going to take the last frame'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as a reference image and generate the next part of the sequence. This time the prompt is the cute mage does a magic spell that transforms the hat in her hand into a fireball. &gt;&gt; And there it is.'

[02:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now she\'s actually casting a spell and transforming the hat into a fireball. But we can extend it one more time. Again, I\'m going to take the last frame as a reference image and the prompt is the cute mage does a fire spell.'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And look at that. Now we have a full'

[02:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'animation sequence where she takes off her hat, turns it into a fireball, and then casts a spell with it. And of course, I\'m going to go ahead and clean it up again before we move on. Next, I\'m going to use this Egyptian cat'

[02:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'goddess that I made. For this example, I\'m using a 256 by 256 canvas, which is another really cool thing about this tool. Even at 256 by 256, we can generate eight animation frames, which'

[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we didn\'t have before even with the pro tools. For this example, I want to show you guys a little tip. Instead of writing the animation prompt myself, I\'m going to go to Gemini, send it the image of my character, and ask it to give me a short'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'paragraph describing an attack animation. The reason I do this is because if you just write something simple like attack, the model will try something, but it might not be exactly what you imagined. When you give it a more descriptive'

[03:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt, you usually get better results. So, I\'m going to take the paragraph Gemini gave me, paste it in here, and generate the animation. Look at that. Pretty nice, right?'

[03:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next, I want to show you that you can really use any LLM to help you generate animation prompts. This time I\'m going to ask Claude to generate a small paragraph describing a tree swaying in the wind.'

[03:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Claude gave me a prompt that mentions things like 60 to 90 frames at 12 frames per second, which obviously doesn\'t'

[04:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'apply here. So, I\'m just going to take the parts that describe the motion and paste that in. And there we go. We get a really nice'

[04:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'animation of the tree swaying with the wind. Before we finish, let\'s go back to the mage. Let\'s add a hit reaction animation and a fire spell forward. So, first let\'s go with the hit reaction. I\'m going to'

[04:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt the mage gets hit and reacts with a dramatic emote. Well, she doesn\'t seem to be really hurt, but it\'s still a reaction'

[04:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'animation and an emote. Let\'s try asking ChatGPT to help us with the prompt. I\'m going to ask it again for a small paragraph describing a hit animation, and I\'m just going to copy and paste it and click generate.'

